The paper discusses the application of reinforcement learning (RL) with human knowledge, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study involves human participants, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The evaluation of different methods for injecting human knowledge into RL involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves the optimization of RL, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
